  "prompt": "Why are people on Quora so snarky?",
  "response": "The perception that people on Quora are snarky can stem from several factors, which are common in many online communities:\n\n1. **Anonymity and Distance**: The internet provides a level of anonymity and physical distance that can embolden people to express themselves more bluntly or sarcastically than they might in face-to-face interactions. Without immediate social repercussions, some users may indulge in snarkiness.\n\n2. **Competition for Attention**: Quora is a platform where insights and answers can earn upvotes, followers, and recognition. Some users might resort to snarky comments as a way to stand out, demonstrate wit, or assert intellectual dominance in a competitive environment.\n\n3. **Frustration with Repetition**: Quora often hosts similar questions repeatedly, which can lead to irritation among long-time users. This frustration might manifest as snarky responses when answering what they perceive as lazy or uninformed questions.\n\n4. **Cultural Norms of the Platform**: Online communities can develop their own norms and cultures. If snarkiness is tolerated or even rewarded with likes and attention, it can become a prevalent communication style within that community.\n\n5. **Age and Experience**: Quora has a diverse user base, and younger or less experienced users might misinterpret sarcasm or dry wit as snarkiness. Additionally, more experienced users might use snark as a way to critique the lack of depth or rigor in certain questions or answers.\n\n6. **Misinterpretation of Tone**: Text-based communication lacks non-verbal cues, making it easy to misinterpret the tone of a message. What is intended as a light-hearted or humorous comment can come across as snarky without the context of vocal inflection or facial expressions.\n\n7. **Defensive Reactions**: Sometimes, when users feel their opinions are being dismissed or attacked, they may respond with snark as a defense mechanism.\n\nIt's important to note that not all users on Quora are snarky, and many engage in thoughtful, respectful, and informative discussions. The platform's community guidelines encourage helpful and polite discourse, and many users adhere to these principles. However, like any large online community, there will always be a range of behaviors and communication styles.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
